# DaisyUI 5

- Docs: https://daisyui.com
- Editor guide: https://daisyui.com/docs/editor/
- Release notes: https://daisyui.com/docs/v5/
- Upgrade guide: https://daisyui.com/docs/upgrade/

## Install & project alignment

- Tailwind CSS 4 is required; we already import it in `src/assets/styles/index.css` with `@import 'tailwindcss';` and `@plugin "daisyui";`.
- Avoid custom global CSS; prefer DaisyUI classes + Tailwind utilities.

## Usage rules

1. Prefer DaisyUI component classes plus Tailwind utilities. Avoid custom CSS.
2. You may tweak via utilities; if specificity blocks, use the `!` suffix sparingly (e.g., `bg-red-500!`).
3. Keep layouts responsive using Tailwind responsive prefixes (e.g., `sm:`, `lg:`).
4. Use only valid DaisyUI class names or Tailwind utilities.
5. Respect theme by using semantic colors (e.g., `bg-primary`, `text-base-content`).
6. Root element should include `id='my-ext'` and `data-theme`.

## Common components (snippets)

```tsx
